Once phase 0 is completed. How can we check it and how is it used?

hecking Phase 0 and What Happens Next
There are three distinct layers of checking — data integrity, model quality, and scientific validity — each with concrete commands and pass/fail criteria. Then the outputs feed directly into three parallel downstream uses.

Layer 1 — Data Integrity Check
Run immediately after the SLURM merge job completes. Takes 2 minutes.

# scripts/check_dataset.py
import h5py
import numpy as np

f = h5py.File("data/mre_synthetic_50000.h5", "r")

# ── Shape checks ──────────────────────────────────────────
assert f["X"].shape == (50000, 4, 64, 64), "Wrong X shape"
assert f["Y"].shape == (50000, 64, 64),    "Wrong Y shape"

# ── Range checks ──────────────────────────────────────────
X = f["X"][:]
Y = f["Y"][:]

assert np.isfinite(X).all(),  "X contains NaN or Inf"
assert np.isfinite(Y).all(),  "Y contains NaN or Inf"
assert Y.min() >= 500,         "Stiffness below physical floor"
assert Y.max() <= 50_000,      "Stiffness above physical ceiling"

# ── Diversity check ───────────────────────────────────────
# G values should not be degenerate (all background, no inclusions)
G_std_per_sample = Y.std(axis=(-2,-1))
assert G_std_per_sample.mean() > 500, "Suspiciously uniform G maps"

# ── Channel check ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Re and Im channels should be correlated but not identical
corr = np.corrcoef(X[:,0].ravel(), X[:,1].ravel())[0,1]
assert abs(corr) < 0.99, "Re and Im channels are identical — solver bug"

# ── Seed uniqueness check (no duplicate cases) ────────────
sample_hashes = [hash(Y[i].tobytes()) for i in range(0, 50000, 500)]
assert len(set(sample_hashes)) == len(sample_hashes), "Duplicate samples found"

print("✓ Dataset integrity: PASS")
print(f"  Samples    : {f['X'].shape[0]:,}")
print(f"  G range    : {Y.min():.0f} – {Y.max():.0f} Pa")
print(f"  G std mean : {G_std_per_sample.mean():.0f} Pa (diversity check)")
