Layer 3 — Scientific Validity Check
Three targeted experiments. Each takes about 30 minutes.
3a. Noise ablation
Rerun inference on the test set with artificial noise added at specific SNR levels. Plot RL² vs SNR. This answers: at what SNR does the FNO start to fail?
3b. Physics loss ablation
Compare the best.pt (trained with Helmholtz penalty) against a checkpoint trained with λ=0 (data loss only). Compute SSIM specifically at inclusion boundaries — a 3-pixel strip around the inclusion edge. If the physics loss improves boundary SSIM by > 0.05 that is a publishable finding.
3c. Inference speed benchmark
