How Phase 0 Outputs Are Used
Use 1 — Directly into Phase 1 (BioQIC transfer)
The best.pt checkpoint is loaded as a pre-trained model and run zero-shot on BioQIC phantom displacement fields. You do not retrain — you just call model(X_bioqic) and compare the predicted stiffness map to the BioQIC ground truth elastogram. The gap between Phase 0 validation RL² and BioQIC RL² is the sim-to-real gap, which tells you how much fine-tuning you will need when Mayo data arrives.
python# Phase 1 entry point — nothing changes except the data loader
model = FNO2d()
model.load_state_dict(torch.load("runs/phase0/best.pt")["model_state"])

bioqic_u = load_bioqic_displacement("bioqic/phantom_60Hz.nii.gz")
G_pred   = model(bioqic_u)
