Use 3 — The Ehman meeting deliverable
The three-panel benchmark figure and the stratified error table are the two slides. The framing for Dr. Ehman is:

"This is what the FNO predicts from synthetic displacement fields. The RL² is X%. We are now ready to run this zero-shot on your BioQIC phantom data — we only need the raw displacement volumes, not the stiffness maps, since we generate our own predictions. The question is how far off we are before any fine-tuning on your data."

That framing is important — it positions Phase 1 as a measurement (how big is the sim-to-real gap?) rather than a request (please give us data to train on). Dr. Ehman is far more likely to share raw displacement volumes if you are already showing results and asking a specific scientific question than if you are asking for training data for an unproven model.


